This lemma calculates the probability of a singleton set `{G}` under the binomial distribution. This probability is given by `p^k * (1-p)^(n-k)` where `k` is the number of edges in `G` and `n` is the total number of possible edges. This is the probability mass function of a binomial distribution with parameters `n` and `p`.

